cs.SY, cs.CE, cs.ET, cs.PF, cs.NI

Reasoning: 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control): The paper proposes a coordinated operation between power distribution system and urban transportation system, which involves control and optimization of both systems.
- cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science): The paper uses simulation and numerical analysis to demonstrate the feasibility and effectiveness of the proposed approach.
- cs.ET (Emerging Technologies): The paper discusses the use of emerging electric vehicles and charging/discharging stations in the coordinated operation.
- cs.PF (Performance): The paper aims to mitigate the operation challenges in each system, which can improve the performance of both systems.
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture): The paper may involve communication and networking between the power distribution system and the urban transportation system.
